## Goal
On-demand git data fetching when rerank preset needs it but data is missing.

## Use Cases (Fallback)
- Background enrichment not yet completed
- Enrichment failed for some files
- Minimal storage mode (don't pre-compute unused metrics)

## Implementation
```typescript
async function rerank(results: SearchResult[], preset: string) {
  const needsGitData = ['techDebt', 'hotspots', 'codeReview', 'ownership'].includes(preset);
  const needsImportedBy = preset === 'impactAnalysis';

  // Check if enrichment data exists
  const missingGit = needsGitData && results.some(r => \!r.payload.fileChurnCount);
  const missingDeps = needsImportedBy && results.some(r => \!r.payload.importedBy);

  if (missingGit || missingDeps) {
    // On-demand enrichment for these specific files
    const filesToEnrich = results
      .filter(r => \!r.payload.fileChurnCount || \!r.payload.importedBy)
      .map(r => r.payload.relativePath);

    await enrichFiles(filesToEnrich, { git: missingGit, deps: missingDeps });

    // Re-fetch results with enriched data
    return refetchAndRerank(results, preset);
  }

  return applyRerank(results, preset);
}
```

## Notes
- Low priority - two-phase indexing covers 95% of cases
- Adds latency to first query if data missing (~200-500ms)
- Consider caching enriched data for subsequent queries

